Get started

Mauro Lepore

2018-04-13

Source: vignettes/fgeo.Rmd

Overview

fgeo installs and loads multiple R packages and functions in a single step. It provides a wide range of tools to analyse forest diversity and dynamics.

  • To learn more about the structure of ForestgGEO’s software see this article.

  • To get started run this:

# install.packages("remotes")
# remotes::install_github("fgeo")
library(fgeo)
#> -- Attaching packages -------------------------------------------- fgeo 0.0.0.9000 --
#> v bciex           0.0.0.9000     v fgeo.habitat    0.0.0.9001
#> v fgeo.abundance  0.0.0.9002     v fgeo.map        0.0.0.9203
#> v fgeo.demography 0.0.0.9000     v fgeo.tool       0.0.0.9002
#>

(See installation.)

  • To search packages and functions, type on the search field, and click the links to learn more.
